---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Safety & Protocols" description="How Adams Farm socializes puppies safely during the critical early window — grounded in current veterinary behavior science.">
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Our Approach</p>
      <h1>Safety &amp; Protocols</h1>
      <p class="page-intro">Early socialization, done responsibly &mdash; and why waiting carries a greater risk.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section page-section">
    <div class="container prose-narrow">
      <p>One of the most common questions we hear is about taking puppies out into the world before their full vaccine series is finished. It&rsquo;s a fair question, and it deserves a straight answer grounded in what the science actually says.</p>

      <h2 class="prose-h2">The window doesn&rsquo;t wait</h2>
      <p>A puppy&rsquo;s socialization window opens early and closes at around 12 to 14 weeks &mdash; well before the standard vaccine schedule is complete. That creates a real tension: the weeks that matter most for a dog&rsquo;s lifelong temperament overlap with the weeks before full immunity. Waiting for the vaccine series to finish doesn&rsquo;t sidestep the risk &mdash; it means missing the window entirely.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="s-standout">
    <div class="container prose-narrow">
      <h2 class="standout-h2">What the veterinary science says</h2>
      <p class="standout-body">The American Veterinary Society of Animal Behavior has taken a clear position: for most puppies, thoughtful early socialization should begin well before the vaccine series is complete. In their view, the behavioral fallout of under-socialization &mdash; the fear and reactivity that lead so many dogs to be given up or put down &mdash; is a greater threat to a dog&rsquo;s life than the disease risk of responsible early exposure. Under-socialization, statistically, is the more dangerous path.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section page-section">
    <div class="container prose-narrow">
      <h2 class="prose-h2">What &ldquo;responsible&rdquo; means in practice</h2>
      <p>Responsible early exposure isn&rsquo;t the dog park. It means:</p>
      <ul class="protocol-list">
        <li>Controlled, chosen settings &mdash; not places where dogs of unknown vaccination status may have been.</li>
        <li>Healthy, known dogs only &mdash; never unfamiliar dogs whose history we can&rsquo;t verify.</li>
        <li>Avoiding high-risk surfaces where disease tends to linger.</li>
        <li>Following our veterinarian&rsquo;s guidance on the partial protection a puppy already carries during this period.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Done this way, the world becomes a classroom without becoming a hazard.</p>

      <p class="prose-emphasis">This is the heart of how we raise calm puppies: not by keeping them sheltered until it&rsquo;s convenient, but by bringing them into the world carefully, at the age when it does the most good.</p>

      <div class="page-cta">
        <a href="/our-program" class="btn btn-primary">See the full PuppyQ approach &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero h1 { color: var(--color-cream-d); }
  .page-hero .page-intro { color: rgba(247, 242, 231, 0.72); }

  .page-section { background: var(--color-white); }
  .prose-narrow {
    max-width: 680px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 20px;
  }
  .prose-narrow p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.78;
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
  }
  .prose-h2 {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--color-pine);
    margin: 12px 0 0;
  }
  .protocol-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 22px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .prose-emphasis {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.15rem !important;
    color: var(--color-pine) !important;
  }

  /* AVSAB standout band — pine, matching the homepage's standout sections */
  .s-standout {
    background: var(--color-pine);
    padding: 56px 0;
  }
  .standout-h2 {
    color: var(--color-card);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .standout-body {
    color: rgba(220, 229, 219, 0.85);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.78;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .page-cta {
    margin-top: 12px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 20px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
</style>
